In [11]:
bins = (0,0.1,0.2,0.3,0.6,1.1)
labels = ['Not Active','Less than average','Average','Active','Super Active']

sample_users['activity_clustering'] = pd.cut(sample_users['activity'],
                                             bins = bins, labels=labels)

In [ ]:
# compute for missing education condition
census_data['college_level'] = np.NaN
numStudents = census_data[['College or associate degree','Bachelor',
                          'Graduate or professional']].sum(axis = 1)
census_data['college_level'] = numStudents / census_data['Total Population']

In [21]:
xs = []
ys = []
zs = []
for each in clustering_plot.activity_clustering.unique():
    if each not in ['']:
        clustering = clustering_plot.loc[clustering_plot.activity_clustering == each]
        xs.append(clustering.college_level.values)
        ys.append(clustering.avg_income.values)
        zs.append(clustering['Density Per Sq Mile'].values)
        print(each)

# Plot for reference value of Census data US
fig = plt.figure()
fig.set_size_inches([12,8])
ax = fig.add_subplot(111,projection = '3d')
ax.scatter(census_data.college_level.values,
          census_data.avg_income.values,
          census_data['Density Per Sq Mile'].values,
           c = 'b', marker = '^',s = 3)
ax.set_xlabel("College %")
ax.set_ylabel('Avg Income $')
ax.set_zlabel('Population Density #')
plt.savefig('CensusDataActClustering.png',
           dpi = 300,
           bbox_inches = 'tight')

In [58]:
'''
Compare active user and super acitve users with Not Active user
'''
clustering_active = sample_users.loc[(sample_users.activity_clustering == 'Super Active') |\
                                     (sample_users.activity_clustering == 'Active')]
print(clustering_active.shape[0] / sample_users.shape[0])
print(clustering_active.avg_income.mean())
clustering_active = clustering_active.loc[clustering_active['Density Per Sq Mile'] > 4000]
print(clustering_active.shape[0] / sample_users.shape[0])
xs = [clustering_active.college_level.values]
ys = [clustering_active.avg_income.values]
zs = [clustering_active['Density Per Sq Mile'].values]
clusteringNotActive = sample_users.loc[sample_users.activity_clustering == 'Not Active'].sample(n = 2000,random_state =0)
xs.append(clusteringNotActive.college_level.values)
ys.append(clusteringNotActive.avg_income.values)
zs.append(clusteringNotActive['Density Per Sq Mile'].values)
college_student = sample_users.loc[sample_users.activity_clustering == 'Less than average']
xs.append(college_student.college_level.values)
ys.append(college_student.avg_income.values)
zs.append(college_student['Density Per Sq Mile'].values)

fig = plt.figure()
fig.set_size_inches([12,8])
ax = fig.add_subplot(111,projection = '3d')

c = ['r','b','g',
    'c','m']
markers = ['o','^','v','*','.']
i = 0
figNumber = 0
ax.scatter(xs[figNumber],ys[figNumber],zs[figNumber],
          c = 'g', marker = '^',s = 2)
figNumber = 1
ax.scatter(xs[figNumber],ys[figNumber],zs[figNumber],
          c = 'r', marker = 'o',s = 4)
#figNumber = 2
#ax.scatter(xs[figNumber],ys[figNumber],zs[figNumber],
#          c = 'c', marker = '*',s = 4)
ax.set_xlabel("College %")
ax.set_ylabel('Avg Income $')
ax.set_zlabel('Population Density #')
ax.legend(['Super Active + Active','Not Active'])
ax.grid()

# import plotly.plotly as py
trace1 = go.Scatter3d(
    x=xs[0],
    y=ys[0],
    z=zs[0],
    mode='markers',
    name = 'Active + Super Active',
    marker=dict(
        size=2,
        
        line=dict(
            color='rgba(217, 217, 217, 0.14)',
            width=0.5
        ),
        opacity=1
    )
)
trace2 = go.Scatter3d(
    x=xs[1],
    y=ys[1],
    z=zs[1],
    mode='markers',
    name = 'Not Active',
    marker=dict(
        size=2,
        symbol = 'circle',
        
        line=dict(
            color='rgb(127, 127, 127)',
           
            width=0.5
        ),
        opacity=0.9
    )
)

data = [trace1,trace2]
layout = go.Layout(
    margin=dict(
        l=0,
        r=0,
        b=0,
        t=0
    ),
    xaxis = dict(
        title = 'College',
    ),
    yaxis = dict(
        title = 'Income'
    ),
    showlegend=True
)
fig = go.Figure(data=data, layout=layout)
iplot(fig)
